      <section eId="sec_58_120">
        <num>58.120</num>
        <content>
          <p>Any governmental agency acquiring any public project pursuant to the provisions of  to may, at the time of issuing the bonds for such acquisition, provide for additional bonds for extensions and permanent improvements to be placed in escrow and to be negotiated from time to time as proceeds for that purpose may be necessary. Bonds placed in escrow shall, when negotiated, have equal standing with bonds of the same issue.</p>
